<br>
Having spent 2 alt exp points on STA, I realize that I have only gained about 20HP.<br>
<br>
Assuming I continue this until I am able to gain the 10% base HP increase, I would ultimately have about 3520 HP unbuffed.<br>
<br>
Is the abilitly to reach 1500AC+ and 5000HP+ fully buffed worth the investment of a significant portion of my alt exp or does another plan make more sense??<br>
<br>
BB <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#564E39><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ubiasschmias.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bias Schmias</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#F4CC10>(12/27/01 3:40:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Warrior Alt Exp</span><hr size=1> I would think putting the points towards damage avoidance/reduction would make more sense initially than putting it towards increased HP.<br>
<br>
But it really depends on what you do, and what you plan to do.<br>
<br>
Are you going to be the main damage sponge on a raid to kill something that quads for some stupid amount?  your total HP aren't going to be nearly as important as your ability to mitigate the volume of damage.<br>
<br>
If you're going to be one of the warriors running around doing whatever and grouping &amp; killing, either one would be fine.  I can't honestly think of a situation where you should put points towards HP first instead of damage avoidance/etc, though.<br>
